	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103238541949601><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6866&mid=103238541949601>Everyone wants to be a teacher</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6866&mid=103238541949601#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=165754><span id=Scholar>Khaless</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>66 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 18th 5:59 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Funny how many of the post state how you are &quot;supposed to play&quot; your necro, chanter, or whatever. When you start your toon there are stat modifiers so you can build your character to play however you want to, I once met a druid that said he wasn't a healer.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Any stat increase or effect you get can't hurt at some time or another. Personally i hate the caster that runs in circles yelling &quot;GET IT OFF ME&quot;, I let those guys die. I have a shammy and i like lots of AC so when i pull aggro i can just stand there and get off a couple of heals with out spell being interupted, then I can focus on mob trying to beat me down. With a haste item coupled with my speed buff i can do some damage with my staff of living sands, hitting for nearly 50 pts. and having more opportunities to proc, till the damage dealers have time to get to me. Sure I could do more damage with a couple DDs and a dot or 2, but i'd rather have some mana left for heals, nothing more pathetic than a whiney warrior asking why ya didn't heal (JK). <br>So let's put the role back into role playing game and let each person choose how their toon utilizes their stats and racial abilities, and if your way is the only right way, i bow down to you my EQ god.  <br>  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
